<title>Gnonogram Mouse/Keyboard Controls</title>
<p>Manipulation of the grid is achieved either by using the mouse (or trackpad) or by using the keyboard.</p>
<list>
	<item><p>Move grid cursor</p>
			<p> Use the mouse (trackpad) or the keyboard cursor keys (Arrow keys).</p>
			<p> The selected cell is marked by a rectangular coloured line and the corresponding row and column clues are highlighted.</p>
	</item>
	<item><p>Mark a cell filled</p>
		<p><key>Left click</key>  <em>or</em> <key>F</key></p> 
	</item>
	<item><p>Mark a cell empty</p>
		<p><key>Right click</key>  <em>or</em> <key>E</key></p> 
	</item>
	<item><p>Mark a cell unknown</p>
		<p><key>Left double click</key>  <em>or</em> <key>X</key></p>
	</item>
	<item><p>Mark a block filled/empty/unknown</p>
		<list>
		<item><p>Position cursor at one end of block </p></item>
		<item><p>Hold down the corresponding button/key</p></item>
		<item><p>Move cursor to end of block</p></item>
		<item><p>Release button/key.</p></item>
		</list>
	</item>
	<item><p>Increase/decrease font size (and thereby the size of the whole window)</p>
		<p>Position the cursor within the grid.  Press <key>+</key> to increase font size or <key>-</key> to decrease it.</p>
	</item>
	<item><p>To determine the block extent and freedom of a row or column</p>
			<p>Hover the cursor over the clue.  A tooltip appears giving the required information.</p>	
	</item>
</list>
</page>
